title: Twin Bing Grand Fondo
description:
The 8th Annual Twin Bing Classic-Climbing Hill, IA
The Races
A Race (1/2/3): 68 miles (3 laps + hilltop finish) Start- 11:00 am
B Race (Masters' 40+ Open, 4/5, Women & Juniors): 44 miles (2 laps + hilltop finish) Start- 11:05 am
course: Starting at the Sheriff's Sub-Station, the clockwise course (all right turns) will proceed west on D54, north on "Old Hwy 141" (D25), east on D38 past Bronson, and south on K64 back to Climbing Hill. You want hills? We have hills! Big ones, medium rollers, and some flat terrain. Wind? Plan on that, too. Road surfaces are good.
registration:
Day-of at the County Sheriff's Sub-Station in Climbing Hill (located on the only east-west street through town).

Registration opens at 9:15 am and closes at 10:45 am.

Save some time in line: Fill out a Standard Athlete's Release and bring it with you.

Make checks payable to "SC Velo".

Renew your race license now!
notes:
The Center Line Rule will be enforced. Wheels in- Wheels out.
The feed zone will be located on the start/finish hill.
There will be water and bathrooms available at the Sub-Station. Otherwise, come prepared. There's no convenience store in Climbing Hill so don't show up running on fumes or needing food.
directions: From I-29 North or South: Take exit 141 to Sergeant Bluff. Go east on 1st Street. The road becomes D38 after you've passed the Fareway store. Head directly east for about 6 miles to the T-intersection. Turn south on D25 (aka "Old 141"). Don't turn left at Bronson. Follow D25 southeasterly for around 3 miles. Turn east onto D54 and it will take you about 6 miles to Climbing Hill. From Highway 20: Turn south at Moville onto K64 (aka the "Moville Blacktop") and follow it to Climbing Hill.

title: Chris Lillig Memorial Cup/Old Capitol Criterium
Race Like A Girl
description: Race Like A Girl - Track style road racing on a closed half-mile loop in Union Park. Each racer will be able to compete several times during the evening for great training. Women are encouraged to come give racing a try! Advanced women are encouraged to enter the A and B race to gain excellent race experience and training!
course: Half-mile loop in Union Park - south end. On street parking or at Birdland Marina/park. Races will be decided into A, B and Novice - Novice women are encouraged to join for great racing practice!
registration: $15 on-site race day registration only. Registration, at the south end of the southern loop, opens at 4:30. First race begins at 5:30.
notes: Velorosa will be collecting items for the Urban Bicycle Food Ministry - please bring bug spray in May.
directions: Union Park is north of University Ave. on Pennsylvania Avenue. Street parking is available around the south edge of the park and in the Birdland Marina parking lot just west of Union Park.

title: 38th Annual Melon City Criterium/ Rider Development
Summerset Shootout presented by Rasmussen Bike Shop
description: Back in the 1930s, the state park was home to one of Iowa’s largest strip mines. Over the past six-plus years, the Central Iowa Trail Association in cooperation with the Iowa DNR has transformed the abandoned strip mine into over five miles of narrow tread, hilly, tight and twisty single track.
course: Full lap at Banner is 5.25–5.5 miles and includes Coal Miner’s Daughter (with black sections), New Ed Beach, Missing Link, Corner Pocket (black), park road, Riverside, park road, and Extra Credit (black).  Click event website for more information.
registration:
**9:00am Trail Run - 1 full lap. Race day registration only for trail race. $20
**10:30am Fat Bike Race - 1 lap w/o advanced sections.  Race day registration only for fat bike race (no pre-registration). $20.  Must be 3.6 tires or greater.
notes:
On-site registration for the trail run opens at 7:45 a.m.
On-site registration for the mountain bike races opens at 8:45 a.m.
Registration ends 30 minutes prior to each race.
Registration and start/finish are located at the 2nd parking lot from the park entrance.
No racer parking in the registration lot. Park in the first lot or the boat ramp lot past the start/finish line.
There is no running water available, and the two toilets are primitive pit toilets
Some drinking water will be available at the registration tent.
Classes may be combined and races be shortened if conditions warrant.
directions:
Banner Lakes at Summerset State Park
Carlisle, Iowa
Highway 65 between Des Moines and Indianola

title: Ingawanis Shredfest
description: Viva La Ingie, It is coming back in to IMBCS race card this year. The land is coming off a big year last year in 2015 an is poised to close out 2016 in fabolous shape. With that said, all proceeds from this Race are going to Bremer County Conservation for the exclusive use for Ingawanis Woodland Trails.
course: The trail system has 7.5 miles of single track.  We will be racing 6 miles of it.
registration: Please register online, this race will have a field limit cap of 125 people.
directions: Ingawanis Woodland Trails, Take 218 exit at Janesville.  Head East on 275th , turn left on to Hawthrone and head north.  After crossing the intersection with 260th, turn into the 2nd driveway on the left.
